<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="912" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d912">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>No. 912<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Representative on the Allied
                                    Commission on Reparations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PEW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Pauley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Delegation to the Allied
                                        Commission on Reparations</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-22">July 22 [<hi rend="italic">21?</hi>], 1945</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><gloss target="#t_Victory1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi></gloss>
                                190. Reference your cable of July 18.<note n="1" xml:id="d912fn1"><ref target="#d899">document No. 899</ref>.</note> (To
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SRG1">Sproul</persName> from <persName corresp="#p_DMGJR1">Deane</persName> from <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName> for <persName corresp="#p_AM1">Abramovitz</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BA1">Bergson</persName>) Please send at once the
                                following additional information <hi rend="italic">one</hi>
                                approximate estimate of value of industrial and mining output in
                                Russian zone in 1938 <hi rend="italic">two</hi> approximate
                                estimated value of agricultural production in the same zone <hi rend="italic">three</hi> approximate percentage that each of the
                                above constitute of total pre-war German production <hi rend="italic">four</hi> approximate percentage of total German
                                industrial and mining production that came from area east of Oder
                                Neisse river[s] in 1939. Above information needed urgently.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>